Reasoning: 
- cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the decentralized control of a team of agents. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper discusses the coordination of agents to accomplish tasks. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is relevant as the paper uses Linear Temporal Logic (LTL) to express local tasks. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper proposes a framework for controlling a team of agents. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the automata-theoretic approach to LTL model checking.
